==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: mandarin duck
<hw>mandarin duck</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>A showy crested Asiatic duck
(<spn>Aix galericulata</spn>, formerly <spn>Dendronessa
galericulata</spn>), often domesticated, and regarded by the Chinese as
an emblem of conjugal affection.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> + <source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 890 --></p>

<p><ent>Mandarinic</ent>⟦br⟧
